## 🗺️ PART 3 — Architecture (How the Parts Connect)

```
BROWSER (React App)
    │
    │  HTTP REST calls (/api/auth, /api/quiz)
    │  ──────────────────────────────────────►
    │                                        EXPRESS SERVER (port 5000)
    │                                           │
    │  WebSocket (Socket.IO, real-time)         ├── Routes → Controllers → MongoDB
    │  ◄──────────────────────────────────────►│
    │                                           └── Socket.IO Events
    │
    └── LocalStorage (saves JWT token)
```

**Key Concept:** There are TWO communication channels:
1. **HTTP REST** — For loading data (login, create quiz, fetch quiz details)
2. **WebSocket (Socket.IO)** — For real-time events during a live quiz (answer submitted, leaderboard updated, timer synced)

