## 💡 PART 8 — Key Technical Concepts to Know

| Concept | What it means in this project |
|---|---|
| **JWT (JSON Web Token)** | A signed digital ID card. Created at login, sent with every request in the `x-auth-token` header. Expires in 1 hour. |
| **bcrypt** | A one-way password hashing function. The plain password is NEVER stored. Only the hash is saved. `bcrypt.compare()` verifies login. |
| **Socket.IO Room** | A named group sockets can join. `socket.join(quizId)` — any message emitted `io.to(quizId)` goes to ALL sockets in that group. |
| **Map (JavaScript)** | Used for in-memory storage: `roomParticipants`, `roomState`, `socketToUser`. These are fast lookups but reset when server restarts. |
| **Mongoose populate()** | When you store a reference (like `student: ObjectId`), `.populate('student', 'username')` replaces the ID with actual user data from the Users collection. |
| **Middleware** | Code that runs BETWEEN receiving a request and handling it. [authMiddleware.js](file:///c:/Users/manim/OneDrive/Desktop/kahoot_team2026/Demo_project/server/middleware/authMiddleware.js) is a middleware that checks the JWT token. |
| **CORS** | Cross-Origin Resource Sharing — allows the React app (on port 5173) to talk to the Express server (on port 5000). |
| **Optimistic Update** | In `submit_question_answer`, progress is marked as answered IMMEDIATELY in memory, then the DB is updated. This makes the UI feel instant. |

